# Arc: Other | Scene: postEscapeLethramShip
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "In the days that followed, the situation on the ship quickly grew dire."
    new "In the days that followed, the situation on the ship quickly grew dire."

    old "Build for a crew of dozens, they struggled to house and care for the nearly thousand on board."
    new "Build for a crew of dozens, they struggled to house and care for the nearly thousand on board."

    old "Rations were enforced from the start. The greatest fear would be running out food."
    new "Rations were enforced from the start. The greatest fear would be running out food."

    old "But with so little to eat, the already stressed survivors, only became more anxious."
    new "But with so little to eat, the already stressed survivors, only became more anxious."

    old "Fights and thefts quickly became common place."
    new "Fights and thefts quickly became common place."

    old "The captain did his best to instill discipline, but even he could only do so much."
    new "The captain did his best to instill discipline, but even he could only do so much."

    old "His sailors remained loyal, but there was always the risk that the people on their ship would turn on them."
    new "His sailors remained loyal, but there was always the risk that the people on their ship would turn on them."

    old "And even hardened sailors could not fight off a mob like that."
    new "And even hardened sailors could not fight off a mob like that."

    old "Each day was counted a blessing, a day closer to the city of Rahayal. Safety."
    new "Each day was counted a blessing, a day closer to the city of Rahayal. Safety."

    old "And each passing day also meant more troubles. More anger. Starvation. Boredom."
    new "And each passing day also meant more troubles. More anger. Starvation. Boredom."

    old "Sarah herself helped the captain as best she could, trying to keep the people calm."
    new "Sarah herself helped the captain as best she could, trying to keep the people calm."

    old "Sure, she had her powers, but if she were to use her magical fire on the ship, it would burn and she would drown along with them on the open sea."
    new "Sure, she had her powers, but if she were to use her magical fire on the ship, it would burn and she would drown along with them on the open sea."

    old "Her only hope was that everyone else understood that their only hope of survival was in cooperation."
    new "Her only hope was that everyone else understood that their only hope of survival was in cooperation."

    old "On the seventh day, when the people had run out of food and reached their limit, the situation peaked."
    new "On the seventh day, when the people had run out of food and reached their limit, the situation peaked."

    old "Someone accused of stealing food had been thrown over board."
    new "Someone accused of stealing food had been thrown over board."

    old "Another proclaimed it had been a lie, and that the man had been innocent."
    new "Another proclaimed it had been a lie, and that the man had been innocent."

    old "Fights. Anger. Screaming."
    new "Fights. Anger. Screaming."

    old "They balanced on a riot. Mutiny."
    new "They balanced on a riot. Mutiny."

    old "Only for a man from the crow's nest to deliver them all from their madness."
    new "Only for a man from the crow's nest to deliver them all from their madness."

    old "Sailor\" \"Land! Rahayal!!!"
    new "Sailor\" \"Land! Rahayal!!!"

    old "He screamed as loudly as he could, no less afraid of the direction that the mob was moving in."
    new "He screamed as loudly as he could, no less afraid of the direction that the mob was moving in."

    old "Then, all at once, the spell of madness broke."
    new "Then, all at once, the spell of madness broke."

    old "Anger and rage faded, the fights stopped, and even those close to starving, began to cheer."
    new "Anger and rage faded, the fights stopped, and even those close to starving, began to cheer."

    old "The cheering of some grew into a loud chorus, as all the survivors on the ship cried out as one."
    new "The cheering of some grew into a loud chorus, as all the survivors on the ship cried out as one."

    old "They had been saved."
    new "They had been saved."

    old "They had survived the fall of Lethram. Survived their torturous journey. Land."
    new "They had survived the fall of Lethram. Survived their torturous journey. Land."

    old "They would live."
    new "They would live."

    old "People fell to their knees, weeping with abandon."
    new "People fell to their knees, weeping with abandon."

    old "With order restored, the Captain regained control of the ship."
    new "With order restored, the Captain regained control of the ship."

    old "The sailors were left to manage the last of the voyage without threat of the mob."
    new "The sailors were left to manage the last of the voyage without threat of the mob."

    old "And so, the ship managed the last miles, slowly pulling into the city of Rahayal."
    new "And so, the ship managed the last miles, slowly pulling into the city of Rahayal."

    old "Sarah was on the top deck when she saw the city draw closer and closer."
    new "Sarah was on the top deck when she saw the city draw closer and closer."

    old "A city unlike any other in the world."
    new "A city unlike any other in the world."

    old "She had been here with Xan, many years ago, and he had shown her about."
    new "She had been here with Xan, many years ago, and he had shown her about."

    old "Sarah remembered being overwhelmed by the sights of it all."
    new "Sarah remembered being overwhelmed by the sights of it all."

    old "Her own home, Castle Reinmeer, in Rosanna, was a hovel compared to this."
    new "Her own home, Castle Reinmeer, in Rosanna, was a hovel compared to this."

    old "Sarah had grown up reading books with carefully drawn images, that spoke of this impossible city."
    new "Sarah had grown up reading books with carefully drawn images, that spoke of this impossible city."

    old "But no words or images could hope to do it justice."
    new "But no words or images could hope to do it justice."

    old "The great hills upon which the city sat, loomed large, build over and populated by countless, the city was almost like an anthill."
    new "The great hills upon which the city sat, loomed large, build over and populated by countless, the city was almost like an anthill."

    old "Carefully, the ship sailed through the vast canals."
    new "Carefully, the ship sailed through the vast canals."

    old "This was a large warship, but in this place, everything felt small."
    new "This was a large warship, but in this place, everything felt small."

    old "Watching the docks as they sailed in, Sarah could see crowds gathered."
    new "Watching the docks as they sailed in, Sarah could see crowds gathered."

    old "They were looking at them, in awe and worry."
    new "They were looking at them, in awe and worry."

    old "No doubt the words of their disaster had spread by ships that had come into the harbor earlier."
    new "No doubt the words of their disaster had spread by ships that had come into the harbor earlier."

    old "Even now, the greatest empire in the world, was quickly learning what doom had fallen on Lethram."
    new "Even now, the greatest empire in the world, was quickly learning what doom had fallen on Lethram."

    old "A nervous panic."
    new "A nervous panic."

    old "These people, safe, feared the arrival of so many fleeing."
    new "These people, safe, feared the arrival of so many fleeing."

    old "For what could they bring, other than trouble?"
    new "For what could they bring, other than trouble?"

    old "Sarah felt her heart grow heavy as the ship finally docked."
    new "Sarah felt her heart grow heavy as the ship finally docked."

    old "At least this city was safe. But her work was far from over."
    new "At least this city was safe. But her work was far from over."

    old "She watched the gangplanks fall from the ship, striking the dock side with a hard clattering sound."
    new "She watched the gangplanks fall from the ship, striking the dock side with a hard clattering sound."

    old "Almost instantly, the crowd on the ship began to surge forward, people frantically surging forward."
    new "Almost instantly, the crowd on the ship began to surge forward, people frantically surging forward."

    old "They were safe, and still they were eager for the certainty of solid ground under their feet."
    new "They were safe, and still they were eager for the certainty of solid ground under their feet."

    old "Sarah watched the masses she had helped save, disembark."
    new "Sarah watched the masses she had helped save, disembark."

    old "There must have been more than a thousand souls, she guessed."
    new "There must have been more than a thousand souls, she guessed."

    old "Why, she wondered, did it still feel as if she failed?"
    new "Why, she wondered, did it still feel as if she failed?"

    old "Sarah heard the soft footsteps of Samayra."
    new "Sarah heard the soft footsteps of Samayra."

    old "You did well."
    new "You did well."

    old "These people are alive because of you."
    new "These people are alive because of you."

    old "I wished the voice in my head sounded more like yours."
    new "I wished the voice in my head sounded more like yours."

    old "More forgiving."
    new "More forgiving."

    old "She heard Samayra sigh."
    new "She heard Samayra sigh."

    old "I've told you many times how incredible you are."
    new "I've told you many times how incredible you are."

    old "How you've saved countless people...and saved me..."
    new "How you've saved countless people...and saved me..."

    old "Sarah turned and saw Samayra's stern face."
    new "Sarah turned and saw Samayra's stern face."

    old "I wish you could see how I see you. How all these people see you."
    new "I wish you could see how I see you. How all these people see you."

    old "Sarah looked out and saw the awed faces among the moving crowd."
    new "Sarah looked out and saw the awed faces among the moving crowd."

    old "Those few that dared to quickly glance at their savior."
    new "Those few that dared to quickly glance at their savior."

    old "And what if it's not enough?"
    new "And what if it's not enough?"

    old "Not enough for what?"
    new "Not enough for what?"

    old "To save everyone."
    new "To save everyone."

    old "Who ever said you had to save everyone? Who ever told you that you had to save the world?"
    new "Who ever said you had to save everyone? Who ever told you that you had to save the world?"

    old "A long silence lingered."
    new "A long silence lingered."

    old "You ask the impossible of yourself, and then you punish yourself for falling short."
    new "You ask the impossible of yourself, and then you punish yourself for falling short."

    old "In the end..."
    new "In the end..."

    old "In the end the only thing you are compelled to answer, is if you did all you could."
    new "In the end the only thing you are compelled to answer, is if you did all you could."

    old "And you've done more than most would."
    new "And you've done more than most would."

    old "Sarah slowly nodded as she looked out across those she had saved."
    new "Sarah slowly nodded as she looked out across those she had saved."

    old "And again she wished she could replace her inner voice with the soft and gentle voice of Samayra."
    new "And again she wished she could replace her inner voice with the soft and gentle voice of Samayra."

    old "For everything."
    new "For everything."

    old "As the last of the refugees flooded out onto the dock, Sarah decided it was time for her to depart as well."
    new "As the last of the refugees flooded out onto the dock, Sarah decided it was time for her to depart as well."

    old "She walked out across the plank, onto solid ground."
    new "She walked out across the plank, onto solid ground."

    old "As soon as her feet touched the ground, a man rushed up."
    new "As soon as her feet touched the ground, a man rushed up."

    old "He seemed expensively dressed, but possessed with a nervousness."
    new "He seemed expensively dressed, but possessed with a nervousness."

    old "Courier\" \"Miss, excuse me!"
    new "Courier\" \"Miss, excuse me!"

    old "His sharp, high voice cut through the crowd."
    new "His sharp, high voice cut through the crowd."

    old "Courier\" \"Miss Rose, yes?"
    new "Courier\" \"Miss Rose, yes?"

    old "She had barely arived in the city, not even a minute, and already someone was waiting for her."
    new "She had barely arived in the city, not even a minute, and already someone was waiting for her."

    old "Who is asking?"
    new "Who is asking?"

    old "Courier\" \"I am courier, send here on behalf of Master Gilead."
    new "Courier\" \"I am courier, send here on behalf of Master Gilead."

    old "Sarah slowly repeated the name. She recalled having vaguely heard it in the past, though she could not remember exactly when."
    new "Sarah slowly repeated the name. She recalled having vaguely heard it in the past, though she could not remember exactly when."

    old "Courier\" \"Yes, Master Gilead, member of the Noctori, holder of a seat at the Eternal Court."
    new "Courier\" \"Yes, Master Gilead, member of the Noctori, holder of a seat at the Eternal Court."

    old "Courier\" \"My Master has extended to you an invitation."
    new "Courier\" \"My Master has extended to you an invitation."

    old "Sarah frowned even more."
    new "Sarah frowned even more."

    old "I don't know your Master, nor do I much appreciate being ambushed like this."
    new "I don't know your Master, nor do I much appreciate being ambushed like this."

    old "The man nervously nodded."
    new "The man nervously nodded."

    old "Courier\" \"Of course, my apologies for any offense I may have unknowingly caused."
    new "Courier\" \"Of course, my apologies for any offense I may have unknowingly caused."

    old "Courier\" \"However, my Master wished to stress that he believes your cause and his align."
    new "Courier\" \"However, my Master wished to stress that he believes your cause and his align."

    old "Sarah frowns."
    new "Sarah frowns."

    old "What does he know of my cause?"
    new "What does he know of my cause?"

    old "The courier pressed the letter into her hands."
    new "The courier pressed the letter into her hands."

    old "Courier\" \"I know only as much as I am told. My Master can answer any questions you might have."
    new "Courier\" \"I know only as much as I am told. My Master can answer any questions you might have."

    old "The man turned and departed almost as suddenly as he arrived."
    new "The man turned and departed almost as suddenly as he arrived."

    old "Sarah looked down at the letter."
    new "Sarah looked down at the letter."

    old "Some performative niceties. Expensive looking seals and sigils. Signed, your friend and ally, Gilead."
    new "Some performative niceties. Expensive looking seals and sigils. Signed, your friend and ally, Gilead."

    old "She sighed as she pocketed the letter."
    new "She sighed as she pocketed the letter."

    old "Sarah didn't know what to make of it just yet, but it seemed unwise to throw it away without knowing more."
    new "Sarah didn't know what to make of it just yet, but it seemed unwise to throw it away without knowing more."

    old "She remained at the docks for a short while longer, but the captain and his crew were doing well in managing the refugees."
    new "She remained at the docks for a short while longer, but the captain and his crew were doing well in managing the refugees."

    old "It wasn't long before Sarah realized she wasn't needed here anymore."
    new "It wasn't long before Sarah realized she wasn't needed here anymore."

    old "Samayra walked up to her as she looked out over the sea of people."
    new "Samayra walked up to her as she looked out over the sea of people."

    old "What do you think we should do now?"
    new "What do you think we should do now?"

    old "I think we're done here. The crew can manage the rest."
    new "I think we're done here. The crew can manage the rest."

    old "As for the people...I hope the city will be able to provide for them."
    new "As for the people...I hope the city will be able to provide for them."

    old "But if more waves of refugees come...I don't know."
    new "But if more waves of refugees come...I don't know."

    old "Samayra nodded solemnly."
    new "Samayra nodded solemnly."

    old "Both understood that even in a time of crisis, people weren't always so kind hearted."
    new "Both understood that even in a time of crisis, people weren't always so kind hearted."

    old "And those who had little, guarded it carefully from those who had nothing."
    new "And those who had little, guarded it carefully from those who had nothing."

    old "Come, we can go the apartment."
    new "Come, we can go the apartment."

    old "Apartment?"
    new "Apartment?"

    old "Xan had properties all over the world. Of course he'd have one in the most important city in the world."
    new "Xan had properties all over the world. Of course he'd have one in the most important city in the world."

    old "Sarah began to walk down the main road that led away from the harbor and into the city interior."
    new "Sarah began to walk down the main road that led away from the harbor and into the city interior."

    old "Slowly, the smell of the sea faded away and gave way to the smell of the city."
    new "Slowly, the smell of the sea faded away and gave way to the smell of the city."

    old "Bustling carts and trade all around."
    new "Bustling carts and trade all around."

    old "It was strange walking here, in such relative calm, when she knew that just an ocean away, a horde of demons roamed free."
    new "It was strange walking here, in such relative calm, when she knew that just an ocean away, a horde of demons roamed free."

    old "Among the many citizens of Rahayal, she spotted the countless branded faces and chained bodies of the slave caste."
    new "Among the many citizens of Rahayal, she spotted the countless branded faces and chained bodies of the slave caste."

    old "Not only did the Mythran empire practice slavery, the number of slaves in fact outnumbered the regular citizens by a good margin."
    new "Not only did the Mythran empire practice slavery, the number of slaves in fact outnumbered the regular citizens by a good margin."

    old "Sarah felt a revulsion at the sight of it, but she also knew she had not come here to set right all the wrongs of the world."
    new "Sarah felt a revulsion at the sight of it, but she also knew she had not come here to set right all the wrongs of the world."

    old "She needed the help of the Empire if they were to stand a chance."
    new "She needed the help of the Empire if they were to stand a chance."

    old "And that meant ignoring certain truths, if only for now."
    new "And that meant ignoring certain truths, if only for now."

    old "As she turned up an expensive looking street, she followed the route that she had learned by heart."
    new "As she turned up an expensive looking street, she followed the route that she had learned by heart."

    old "In between a set of villas, a stairway laid hidden behind a small alcove."
    new "In between a set of villas, a stairway laid hidden behind a small alcove."

    old "Sarah made sure she and Samayra were not being followed, then headed up the stairs."
    new "Sarah made sure she and Samayra were not being followed, then headed up the stairs."

    old "She produced the single key that opened all of Xan's properties."
    new "She produced the single key that opened all of Xan's properties."

    old "The door creaked and groaned as it swung open."
    new "The door creaked and groaned as it swung open."

    old "A rush of stale air greeted her."
    new "A rush of stale air greeted her."

    old "Nobody had been here in a long time."
    new "Nobody had been here in a long time."

    old "Sarah had not seen a reason to visit Rahayal before now, and Xan obviously hadn't either. Not since she..."
    new "Sarah had not seen a reason to visit Rahayal before now, and Xan obviously hadn't either. Not since she..."

    old "She shook her head, disregarding the thought."
    new "She shook her head, disregarding the thought."

    old "Walking inside, she felt it was quite a bit colder."
    new "Walking inside, she felt it was quite a bit colder."

    old "Nestled between the buildings around it, the apartment offered the kind of privacy that Xan had valued."
    new "Nestled between the buildings around it, the apartment offered the kind of privacy that Xan had valued."

    old "She heard Samayra follow her."
    new "She heard Samayra follow her."

    old "This is quite a place."
    new "This is quite a place."

    old "We can work from here while I figure out what to do next."
    new "We can work from here while I figure out what to do next."

    old "Sarah felt the girl's eyes on her body."
    new "Sarah felt the girl's eyes on her body."

    old "What...are we going to do next?"
    new "What...are we going to do next?"

    old "I don't know...I have to think."
    new "I don't know...I have to think."

    old "I know you'll find the answer."
    new "I know you'll find the answer."

    old "She wished she had the confidence that Samayra had in her."
    new "She wished she had the confidence that Samayra had in her."

    old "I'll get settled in the office. You unpack, okay?"
    new "I'll get settled in the office. You unpack, okay?"

    old "Got it."
    new "Got it."

    old "Sarah made sure she was not being followed, then headed up the stairs."
    new "Sarah made sure she was not being followed, then headed up the stairs."

    old "Without thinking, Sarah put down her belongings in the living room."
    new "Without thinking, Sarah put down her belongings in the living room."

    old "This would have to do as a base."
    new "This would have to do as a base."

    old "At least until she figured out what to do next."
    new "At least until she figured out what to do next."

    old "She sighed and walked over to the office in the back."
    new "She sighed and walked over to the office in the back."

    old "Stepping inside, Sarah saw the small collection of maps and books, still balanced on the desk."
    new "Stepping inside, Sarah saw the small collection of maps and books, still balanced on the desk."

    old "A relic from when Xan had last been here, years ago."
    new "A relic from when Xan had last been here, years ago."

    old "Whatever he had been researching back then, she didn't have a clue."
    new "Whatever he had been researching back then, she didn't have a clue."

    old "As she sat down, the map in the center of the desk drew her attention."
    new "As she sat down, the map in the center of the desk drew her attention."

    old "A detailed map of the city of Rahayal, containing not just all the districts, but even down to recording most streets and alleys."
    new "A detailed map of the city of Rahayal, containing not just all the districts, but even down to recording most streets and alleys."

    old "It was intricate."
    new "It was intricate."

    old "A few marks on the map, notes left by Xan, probably to himself."
    new "A few marks on the map, notes left by Xan, probably to himself."

    old "Sat in the center of the map, a massive black triangular space."
    new "Sat in the center of the map, a massive black triangular space."

    old "The Black Pyramid, home to the Eternal Court."
    new "The Black Pyramid, home to the Eternal Court."

    old "On the map, just as in real life, the thing seemed an abstraction to its surroundings."
    new "On the map, just as in real life, the thing seemed an abstraction to its surroundings."

    old "The Eternal Court ruled the Empire."
    new "The Eternal Court ruled the Empire."

    old "If she wanted any chance to invoke the Empire's support in fighting the Voidlings, she would need to gain an audience with them."
    new "If she wanted any chance to invoke the Empire's support in fighting the Voidlings, she would need to gain an audience with them."

    old "She reached into her pocket and pulled out the letter that she had received from the courier."
    new "She reached into her pocket and pulled out the letter that she had received from the courier."

    old "If he was to be believed, this Gilead person was a member of the Eternal Court."
    new "If he was to be believed, this Gilead person was a member of the Eternal Court."

    old "He might be able to get her the audience she needed."
    new "He might be able to get her the audience she needed."

    old "Still, she worried."
    new "Still, she worried."

    old "It all felt too coincidental to be an accident."
    new "It all felt too coincidental to be an accident."

    old "And she hated the idea of not understanding who he was or what his intentions were."
    new "And she hated the idea of not understanding who he was or what his intentions were."

    old "Not knowing made her susceptible to being used by him."
    new "Not knowing made her susceptible to being used by him."

    old "But Sarah didn't see many other options."
    new "But Sarah didn't see many other options."

    old "She put the letter away again."
    new "She put the letter away again."

    old "She decided she would meet with him, if only to feel him out."
    new "She decided she would meet with him, if only to feel him out."

    old "Still, that was a matter for another night."
    new "Still, that was a matter for another night."

    old "Sarah could feel all the tiredness of the day's events, sinking into her body, all at once."
    new "Sarah could feel all the tiredness of the day's events, sinking into her body, all at once."

    old "She stumbled away from the desk, back into the living room."
    new "She stumbled away from the desk, back into the living room."

    old "Just as she nearly tripped, she felt Samayra's hands catching her."
    new "Just as she nearly tripped, she felt Samayra's hands catching her."

    old "Sarah slowly felt herself regain her footing."
    new "Sarah slowly felt herself regain her footing."

    old "I'm...I'm fine...thanks..."
    new "I'm...I'm fine...thanks..."

    old "No, you're not!"
    new "No, you're not!"

    old "Samayra almost sounded angry."
    new "Samayra almost sounded angry."

    old "Sarah saw the girl's face, contorted in a rare expression of rage."
    new "Sarah saw the girl's face, contorted in a rare expression of rage."

    old "You almost fainted!"
    new "You almost fainted!"

    old "Sarah leaned on Samayra as Samayra carried her to the bedroom."
    new "Sarah leaned on Samayra as Samayra carried her to the bedroom."

    old "She slowly let go of Samayra as she fell into the bed."
    new "She slowly let go of Samayra as she fell into the bed."

    old "Sarah felt so tired, she could almost imagine sinking into the soft sheets."
    new "Sarah felt so tired, she could almost imagine sinking into the soft sheets."

    old "Gods, Sarah..."
    new "Gods, Sarah..."

    old "You really need to take better care of yourself."
    new "You really need to take better care of yourself."

    old "I...I know..."
    new "I...I know..."

    old "She saw Samayra's concerned face."
    new "She saw Samayra's concerned face."

    old "You say that, but you keep pushing yourself. Always pushing yourself."
    new "You say that, but you keep pushing yourself. Always pushing yourself."

    old "You act like the world is on your shoulders and...maybe it is, but what will happen if you don't take care of yourself?"
    new "You act like the world is on your shoulders and...maybe it is, but what will happen if you don't take care of yourself?"

    old "There isn't any shame in taking a moment to yourself."
    new "There isn't any shame in taking a moment to yourself."

    old "You're only human, despite whatever you tell yourself."
    new "You're only human, despite whatever you tell yourself."

    old "Sarah slowly nodded as she felt her eyelids grow heavy."
    new "Sarah slowly nodded as she felt her eyelids grow heavy."

    old "I know...thanks...Samayra."
    new "I know...thanks...Samayra."

    old "She felt the girl crawl into the bed next to her."
    new "She felt the girl crawl into the bed next to her."

    old "Nestling her body up against hers."
    new "Nestling her body up against hers."

    old "More than anything, it was comfortable."
    new "More than anything, it was comfortable."

    old "Sarah felt herself smiling as she wrapped her arms around Samayra."
    new "Sarah felt herself smiling as she wrapped her arms around Samayra."

    old "The girl wrapped her arms around Sarah."
    new "The girl wrapped her arms around Sarah."

    old "And together, the two sank into a deep sleep."
    new "And together, the two sank into a deep sleep."

    old "Sarah on barely managed to make it to the bedroom before collapsing into the bed."
    new "Sarah on barely managed to make it to the bedroom before collapsing into the bed."

    old "Exhaustion dragged her into a deep slumber."
    new "Exhaustion dragged her into a deep slumber."

    old "The next day, Sarah arived at the gate of Gilead's estate."
    new "The next day, Sarah arived at the gate of Gilead's estate."

    old "She had decided to leave Samayra behind."
    new "She had decided to leave Samayra behind."

    old "Whatever risk there was in meeting this Gilead, Sarah intended to carry it alone."
    new "Whatever risk there was in meeting this Gilead, Sarah intended to carry it alone."

    old "As the guards at the gate noticed her approach, they sounded a signal by blowing a horn."
